Variable order PN approximation 

Usage

1. $TOASTVER/bin/rte3D_varOrd <mesh file name>  <    <input file name>

2. $TOASTVER/bin/rte3D_varOrd <mesh file name > <QM file name> < <input file name>

Input files can be generated using the MATLAB script 'generateInputFile.m' script contained in this folder

NOTES: 

1. Currently works only in 'element' basis. Hence mua, mus, ref needs to be specified for each element

2. The files 'genmat_angint_3D_PN.cc' and 'genmat_angint_sdm_3D_PN.cc' and 'spints.cc' are not part of the 
core variable order PN code. They contain time and memory efficient implementations of the angular matrices
and will be integrated and tested into the core program at a later date.
 
3.This code currently works for only boundary sources. If interior sources are required uncomment
'genmat_intsourcevalvector_3D(ctxt.nodal_sphOrder, ctxt.node_angN, ctxt.offset, b2, qmmesh, Nsource[0], dirVec, is_cosine, pts, wts, ctxt.Ylm);' in the source and comment 'genmat_source_3D(ctxt.nodal_sphOrder, ctxt.node_angN, ctxt.offset, Source, qmmesh, Nsource, ns, dirVec, is_cosine, pts, wts, ctxt.b1, ctxt.Ylm);' compile ('make' from 'src' level) and run. Similar compilation should be done when using QM files.

 
